The feedback log shows entries up to FB-224, and the anti-patterns catalog is at AP-072. Next IDs: **FB-225** and **AP-073**.

Here's the complete diagnosis, the three-file fix, and the two documentation updates.

---

## Diagnosis

The logo text `"Yilan Gao"` is wrapping to two lines under flex pressure. The SCSS already has `white-space: nowrap` on `.logoText` and `flex-shrink: 0` on `.logo` — but the **flex container (`.navInner`)** is `justify-content: space-between`, which means the two children (`.logo` and `.links`) compete for whatever width the viewport gives them. When the viewport is squeezed, flex's shrink algorithm first starves `.links`, then — if `.links` has already hit its minimum content width — it will start overflowing or causing the logo to wrap. The real issue is structural: the **`.navInner` row has no protection against its children conflicting**. Because `.logo` has `flex-shrink: 0` but no explicit `min-width: max-content`, and `.links` has `min-width: 0` but no guaranteed right to its own space, browsers can still break the logo text at the word boundary between "Yilan" and "Gao" in certain vendor/version combinations.

## Root Cause

**AP-068** (relying on grid/flex track minimum alone to prevent text wrap in a one-line-per-item list) is the closest existing pattern — but this is a distinct, named variant: `flex-shrink: 0` alone is insufficient when the flex parent's algorithm hasn't been told the logo is inviolable. The correct fix is a **three-layer guarantee**: `flex-shrink: 0` + `white-space: nowrap` (already present on the text) + **`min-width: max-content`** on the logo link itself, so the browser's sizing pass never considers a narrower width as viable. This also needs to be codified as **AP-073** — a new anti-pattern — because the underlying rule ("core identity strings are structurally inviolable, not just stylistically so") is not yet documented.

---

## Fix

### 1. `src/components/ui/Navigation/Navigation.module.scss`

Two surgical changes inside `.logo`:
- Add `min-width: max-content` — makes the flex algorithm treat the logo's full single-line width as the absolute floor. No amount of outer container pressure can shrink it below that.
- Strengthen the existing comment to reference AP-073.

The `.logoText` already has `white-space: nowrap` — that stays. No change needed there.

```scss
@use '../../../styles' as *;

.nav {
  position: sticky;
  top: 0;
  z-index: var(--portfolio-z-sticky);
  background-color: var(--portfolio-surface-terra-subtle);
  box-shadow: 0 4px 12px -4px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);

  &::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    bottom: 0;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    height: 10px;
    transform: translateY(100%);
    backdrop-filter: blur(3px);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(3px);
    mask-image: linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2), transparent);
    -webkit-mask-image: linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2), transparent);
    pointer-events: none;
  }
}

.navInner {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: space-between;
  max-width: $elan-container-wide;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: var(--portfolio-spacer-1-5x) var(--portfolio-spacer-2x);

  @media #{$elan-mq-sm} {
    padding: var(--portfolio-spacer-1-5x) var(--portfolio-spacer-4x);
  }
}

.logo {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: $portfolio-spacer-0-5x;
  text-decoration: none;
  //
  // IDENTITY LOCK — AP-073
  // The logo is the site's primary identity mark. It is structurally
  // inviolable at every viewport width. Three properties work together:
  //
  //   1. flex-shrink: 0        — flex algorithm never steals width from the logo.
  //   2. min-width: max-content — the browser's sizing pass treats the full
  //                               single-line width as the hard floor. No
  //                               container constraint can produce a narrower
  //                               measure and trigger line-break evaluation.
  //   3. white-space: nowrap   — on .logoText, prevents the word "Yilan" and
  //                               "Gao" from splitting even if (1) and (2) are
  //                               somehow overridden by an outer constraint.
  //
  // The element allowed to yield is .tagline, not this element.
  // See AP-073 in docs/design-anti-patterns.md.
  //
  flex-shrink: 0;
  min-width: max-content; // ← THE FIX: hard floor for the flex sizing pass
  @include transition-fast;

  &:hover {
    .logoMark {
      background-color: var(--portfolio-text-neutral-max);
    }

    .logoText {
      color: var(--portfolio-text-neutral-max);
    }
  }
}

.logoMark {
  display: inline-block;
  height: calc($portfolio-type-2xl * 1.2);
  aspect-ratio: 1;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  background-color: $portfolio-accent-60;
  mask-image: url('/images/yg-logo.svg');
  mask-size: contain;
  mask-repeat: no-repeat;
  @include transition-fast;
}

.logoText {
  font-family: $portfolio-font-serif;
  font-size: $portfolio-type-2xl;
  font-weight: $portfolio-weight-regular;
  line-height: $portfolio-leading-snug;
  color: $portfolio-accent-60;
  letter-spacing: $portfolio-tracking-tight;
  white-space: nowrap; // layer 3 of the identity lock — see .logo comment
  @include transition-fast;
}

.links {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: var(--portfolio-spacer-3x);
  // .links is the soft edge of the nav row. It yields first under squeeze
  // pressure via min-width: 0. Its children (especially .tagline) may wrap
  // to two lines. The logo never participates in this yielding.
  min-width: 0;
}

.link {
  font-family: var(--portfolio-font-sans);
  font-size: var(--portfolio-type-sm);
  font-weight: var(--portfolio-weight-regular);
  color: var(--portfolio-text-secondary);
  text-decoration: none;
  @include transition-fast;

  &:hover {
    color: var(--portfolio-text-primary);
  }
}

.linkActive {
  color: var(--portfolio-text-primary);
  font-weight: var(--portfolio-weight-medium);
}

.tagline {
  @include body-sm;
  color: var(--portfolio-text-secondary);
  // The tagline is the soft edge of the nav: it yields to narrow viewports by
  // wrapping onto a second line, capped at two lines so it never invades the
  // site content below. This is the explicit pressure-release valve — so the
  // logo never has to be one.
  min-width: 0;
  text-align: right;
  display: -webkit-box;
  -webkit-box-orient: vertical;
  -webkit-line-clamp: 2;
  line-clamp: 2;
  overflow: hidden;
}
```

