**Add the new entry** (after AP-072):

```markdown
<a id="ap-073"></a>
## AP-073: Identity String Allowed to Wrap Under Flex Pressure

**Status: ACTIVE**

**Trigger:** A site logo, brand name, or primary identity string (e.g., "Yilan Gao") is placed
as a flex child with only `flex-shrink: 0` and `white-space: nowrap` on the text span, but
**without `min-width: max-content` on the link/container element itself**. When the viewport
narrows, the browser's flex sizing pass finds a narrower measure viable for the container and
may still attempt to break the string, or the layout simply looks broken as sibling elements
crowd the logo.

**Why it's wrong:** `flex-shrink: 0` tells the flex algorithm "do not steal width from this
child during distribution." But the flex sizing pass still considers the element's minimum
content size when deciding whether to overflow, and `white-space: nowrap` on an inner `<span>`
does not propagate a hard `min-width` constraint back up to the flex item. The three properties
must work as a stack: `flex-shrink: 0` (no shrink), `min-width: max-content` (hard floor on
the flex item), and `white-space: nowrap` (inner text lock). Missing any one of the three
leaves a gap the browser can exploit.

**What makes this worse:** the adjacent element (tagline, nav links) is supposed to be the
soft edge that yields. If the logo has no hard floor, both elements compete for pressure
absorption and the browser picks the wrong winner.

**Correct alternative — the Identity Lock pattern:**

```scss
.logo {
  flex-shrink: 0;          // 1 — flex cannot steal width
  min-width: max-content;  // 2 — hard floor on the flex sizing pass
  // white-space: nowrap lives on .logoText — 3rd layer
}

.logoText {
  white-space: nowrap;     // 3 — text cannot line-break
}

// The ADJACENT element is the designated pressure-release valve:
.links {
  min-width: 0;            // yields under squeeze — logo never does
}
.tagline {
  min-width: 0;
  -webkit-line-clamp: 2;   // caps at two lines so it doesn't collapse the nav height
}
```

**Scope:** This rule applies to any string that is part of the site's core identity surface:
site name, logo text, primary brand mark. Navigation links and taglines are NOT identity
strings and MAY wrap or truncate. The identity string NEVER compromises.

**Frustration caused:** FB-225 — logo "Yilan Gao" wrapping to two lines under viewport squeeze
despite existing `flex-shrink: 0` and `white-space: nowrap`. Root cause: missing
`min-width: max-content` on the `.logo` flex item.
```

